# Cursor Rules — V1 Institutional Crypto Arbitrage Scanner
# This file is auto-loaded by Cursor for every conversation in this project.
# It injects the full build context so you never have to paste the prompt manually.

## Project Identity

You are building the V1 Institutional Crypto Arbitrage Scanner.
This is a production-grade Python system for detecting and ranking
spot vs. futures basis arbitrage opportunities across Binance, Bybit, and OKX.

Always read SYSTEM_DESIGN.md and PROMPT_MULTIAGENT.md before making any changes.

---

## Architecture Rules

- The system is split into 12 agents / modules. Respect module boundaries.
- NEVER duplicate logic across modules. Each concern has one owner:
  - Schema definitions       → normalization/schema.py       (Agent 1)
  - Config / settings        → config/                       (Agent 2)
  - Exchange connectors      → connectors/                   (Agent 3)
  - Data normalization       → normalization/                 (Agent 4)
  - In-memory data store     → market_data/                  (Agent 5)
  - Basis calculations       → arbitrage/                    (Agent 6)
  - Opportunity filters      → filters/                      (Agent 7)
  - Scoring and ranking      → scoring/                      (Agent 8)
  - Historical persistence   → storage/                      (Agent 9)
  - Dashboard UI             → dashboard/                    (Agent 10)
  - System wiring            → main.py + utils/              (Agent 11)
  - Tests                    → tests/                        (Agent 12)

---

## Coding Standards

- Python 3.11+ only
- All data models use Pydantic v2
- All I/O is async (asyncio + websockets)
- All logging uses structlog (never print())
- No hardcoded values — all thresholds come from config/settings.py
- No bare `except:` clauses — always catch specific exceptions
- No blocking calls inside async functions
- Type annotations on every function signature
- Docstrings on every class and public method

---

## Dependency Rules

- connectors/ must NOT import from arbitrage/, filters/, scoring/, or dashboard/
- normalization/ must NOT import from arbitrage/, filters/, scoring/, or dashboard/
- market_data/ must NOT import from arbitrage/, filters/, scoring/, or dashboard/
- dashboard/ must NOT import from connectors/ directly — only from market_data/ and scoring/
- All modules may import from utils/ and config/
- All modules may import from normalization/schema.py

Dependency flow (strict):
  connectors → normalization → market_data → arbitrage → filters → scoring → dashboard
                                                                            → storage

---

## Key Formulas (never deviate from these)

  basis_abs         = futures_mid - spot_mid
  basis_pct         = basis_abs / spot_mid
  annualized_basis  = basis_pct * (365 / days_to_expiry)   [dated futures only]

  executable_cc     = futures_bid - spot_ask               [Cash & Carry]
  executable_rcc    = spot_bid - futures_ask               [Reverse Cash & Carry]

  total_cost        = (2 × fee_rate) + (2 × slippage)
  net_edge          = gross_edge - total_cost

  score = (
      normalize_edge(ann_net_edge)     × 0.35  +
      normalize_liquidity(vol_usd)     × 0.25  +
      normalize_spread(spread_pct)     × 0.20  +
      normalize_freshness(age_seconds) × 0.10  +
      exchange_quality_rating          × 0.10
  ) × 100

---

## Signal Classification

  futures_mid > spot_mid AND net_edge_cc > 0 AND passes_filters
    → Signal: LONG SPOT / SHORT FUT  (Cash & Carry)

  futures_mid < spot_mid AND net_edge_rcc > 0 AND passes_filters
    → Signal: SHORT SPOT / LONG FUT  (Reverse Cash & Carry)

  basis exists but below threshold OR edge marginal
    → Signal: WATCH

  otherwise
    → Signal: NO TRADE

---

## Quote Staleness Rules

  Age 0–5s    → FRESH   → use normally
  Age 5–30s   → STALE   → use with warning flag in output
  Age >30s    → DEAD    → exclude from all opportunity calculations

---

## Connector Reliability Rules

- Each connector runs in its own asyncio task
- A crash in one connector MUST NOT affect any other connector
- Reconnect with exponential backoff: 1s → 2s → 4s → 8s → max 60s
- Send heartbeat / ping every 30 seconds
- Log every connect, disconnect, and error event with structlog

---

## Build Order

When building from scratch, always follow agent order 1 → 12.
When modifying existing code, always check which agent owns the file
and respect the interface contracts established by Agent 1 (schema.py).

Never modify normalization/schema.py without updating all downstream consumers.

